Ricus Reeders from PSG Wealth Sandton chose Adcock Ingram as his stock pick of the day and Ian Cruickshanks from the SA Institute of Race Relations chose cash. Reeders said: “I’m going with Adcock, they have had decent results, obviously there is always the problem with regulation specifically with the National Health Insurance (NHI) but their over-the-counter market is growing.” Cruickshanks said: “I would tend to go into the US market with a currency hedge first of all and I’d want to go in for a fund which had commercial bonds because I believe if you have any rate cuts it is going to be a capital gain score there.” Or listen to the full audio: Subscribe: iono.fm | Apple Podcasts | Pocket Casts | Player.fm